{
  "texts": [
    "• We propose the multi-modal model named SAM, which employs bidirectional semantic guidance between images of the input multi-modal instruction to align the semantics of different images in the perception stage.",
    "• Extensive experiments prove the effectiveness of our SAM model by significantly outperforming the state-of-the-arts.",
    "2 Related Work Multi-modal Large Language ModelsMulti-modal pretraining [8,17,32,33,42,43,50] aims to train models on varied datasets across multiple modalities to capture cross-modal correlations.",
    "Building upon the concept of multi-modal pretraining, Multi-modal Large Language Models represent a fusion of multi-modal pretraining techniques with the advanced capabilities of Large Language Models.",
    "Flamingo [1] proposes architectural innovations that enable the integration of powerful pre-trained vision-only and language-only models, managing sequences of interleaved visual and textual data, and seamlessly ingesting images or videos as inputs."
  ]
}